ETYMOLOGY: From Old French Septembre, from Latin September (seventh month), from septem 'seven', as it was the seventh month in the early Roman calendar which began in March.

MEANINGS.DEF_EN: The ninth month of the year in the Gregorian calendar, coming after August and before October, usually having 30 days.
MEANINGS.DEF_ZH: 公历中的第九个月，位于八月之后、十月之前，通常有30天。
MEANINGS.SENT_EN: The fall semester begins in September.
